</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="49" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[264,1323,284,1070]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,456,924,950]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Etymology:</emphasis>
Named after the indigenous 
<taxonomicName authority="Indians" authorityName="Indians" box="[805,997,924,950]" class="Insecta" family="Leptohyphidae" genus="Cabecar" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Cabécar Indians</taxonomicName>
, who inhabit the mountains and low­lying Caribbean costal areas of southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[896,1025,964,990]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
and northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1190,1283,964,990]" name="Panama" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Panama</collectingCountry>
on the Talamanca reservation. Their original homeland include the 
<typeStatus box="[1037,1087,1004,1030]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">type</typeStatus>
locality of the new species described herein. Nomenclatural gender: masculine, arbitrarily selected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
